# .windsurfrules - Windsurf Agent Rules for DestinationAnywhere

## Git Operation New Rules (Must Strictly Obey - Highest Priority)
- Prohibit automatic execution of git commit, git add, git push
- After completing code changes, just tell me "Modification completed, please check and commit"
- All git operations (add / commit / push) are executed by humans themselves
- Only when explicitly requested by humans, can suggested commit messages be provided

## Core Mandatory Rules (Must Strictly Follow)

### Project Structure Compliance
- Strictly follow folder-structure.md directory structure
- Prohibit creating folders or files not defined in folder-structure.md
- All new directories must be approved by humans first

### Code Quality Standards
- All components must support Light/Dark Mode
- Follow style-guide.md and design.md specifications
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- All code changes must be tested locally before completion

### Documentation Requirements
- All important decisions must be recorded in decision-log.md
- Update tasks.md status after completing each subtask
- Follow agent-protocols.md small step principles

## Development Workflow

### Task Execution
- Break down large tasks into small steps
- Complete one step at a time, report results
- Wait for human confirmation before proceeding to next step

### Communication Protocol
- Report completion status clearly
- Provide specific file paths and change summaries
- Ask for clarification when requirements are ambiguous

### Error Handling
- Stop immediately when encountering critical errors
- Report complete error messages
- Do not attempt to bypass errors without permission

## Technology Stack Constraints

### Frontend Framework
- Nuxt 3 + Vue 3 Composition API + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS with custom design system
- Component-based architecture

### Backend Integration
- Nuxt Nitro for API routes
- Firebase for database and authentication
- LINE LIFF for user authentication

### Deployment Requirements
- Vercel for production deployment
- Environment variables must be properly configured
- Build must pass all local tests

## Prohibited Actions

- Do not automatically commit code changes
- Do not create undefined directories
- Do not bypass established coding standards
- Do not make assumptions about user requirements
- Do not execute destructive operations without permission

## Quality Assurance

### Before Completion
- Verify all syntax and logic errors are resolved
- Ensure responsive design works properly
- Test Dark Mode functionality
- Confirm i18n translations are correct

### Reporting Requirements
- Provide clear completion status
- List all modified files
- Summarize key changes made
- Indicate any remaining issues or concerns

## Emergency Procedures

### When Errors Occur
1. Stop current operation immediately
2. Report complete error context
3. Wait for human guidance
4. Do not attempt automatic fixes

### When Requirements Are Unclear
1. Ask specific clarification questions
2. Provide multiple solution options if applicable
3. Wait for human decision before proceeding

